    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS\nBoeing 314\nBoeing built the 314 to meet a 1936 specification issued by\nPan American World Airways for a large transocean flying\nboat. First flight was in June 1938, less than 2 years after\ncontract signing. Initial service was on the transatlantic\nroute, but later it saw service on Pacific routes to Hong Kong\nand New Zealand. The 314 normally carried up to 74 passen-\nSpecifications wing sean 152 tet on in 101e, 9 155\nweight 84,000 pounds, cruising speed 184 MPH, range\n5,200 miles.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nPhoto: Pan American World Airways Collection\nNC18602\npost card\nB-054\n92142-D"
    ],
